{"title_page": "Mokalik", "text_new": "{{Short description|2019 Nigerian comedy drama film by Kunle Afolayan}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mokalik\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Kunle Afolayan]]\n| producer       = Kunle Afolayan\n| screenplay     = Tunde Babalola\n| story          = Kunle Afolayan\n| starring       = Toni Afolayan<br>[[Femi Adebayo]]<br>[[Tobi Bakre]]\n| music          = Kentoxygen Egunjobi\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio         = Golden Effects Pictures/Africa Magic\n| distributor    = FilmOne\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|05|31|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 99 minutes\n| country        = Nigeria\n| language       = English<br>Yoruba\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \u20a646.9[[million]]<ref name=cinema>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ceanigeria.com/box-office/2019-overall/122-top-20-wa-films-of-2019|title=TTop 20 films of 2019|publisher=Cinema Exhibitors Association of Nigeria}}</ref>\n| based on       = \n}}\n\n'''''Mokalik''''' ({{lang-en|Mechanic}}) is a 2019 Nigerian bilingual [[Comedy film|comedy]] [[Drama film|drama]] film produced and directed by veteran filmmaker [[Kunle Afolayan]]. The film stars newcomer Toni Afolayan in the male lead role along with [[Femi Adebayo]]. The film had its theatrical release on 31 May 2019 and received extremely positive reviews from critics while also performing well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Movie Review: Kunle Afolayan\u2019s \u2018Mokalik\u2019 thrives on memory, not viewer satisfaction|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/entertainment/nollywood/365003-movie-review-kunle-afolayans-mokalik-thrives-on-memory-not-viewer-satisfaction.html|date=2019-11-24|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Box Office: Nigerian moviegoers spent N636 million in July but less than N20 million went to Nollywood|url=https://www.pulse.ng/bi/lifestyle/box-office-nigerian-moviegoers-spent-n636-million-in-july-but-less-than-n20-million/ds2eh4b|date=2019-08-06|website=www.pulse.ng|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref> It was acquired by [[Netflix]] in July 2019 and was streamed on 1 September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kunle Afolayan's Mokalik, October 1, Now on Netflix|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2019/08/23/kunle-afolayans-mokalik-october-1-now-on-netflix/|last=editor|date=2019-08-23|website=THISDAYLIVE|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Netflix acquires Kunle Afolayan\u2019s \u2018Mokalik\u2019, others|url=https://punchng.com/netflix-acquires-kunle-afolayans-mokalik-others/|last=Published|website=Punch Newspapers|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref> The film has been included as a part of \"Made in Africa\" collection in May 2020 by Netflix to be streamed amid the [[COVID-19 pandemic|global COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Netflix highlights 100+ African titles in new 'Made in Africa' collection|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/netflix-highlights-100-african-titles-in-new-made-in-africa-collection/qkk9787|date=2020-05-05|website=Pulse Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Netflix celebrates Africa Day with Made in Africa collection|url=https://www.htxt.co.za/2020/05/04/netflix-celebrates-africa-day-with-made-in-africa-collection/|last=Lotz|first=Brendyn|date=2020-05-04|website=htxt.africa|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref> The film was also nominated for the Best Film category during the 2019 Durban International Film Festival. The film was also premiered in several film festivals.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Toni Afolayan]] as Ponmile\n* [[Femi Adebayo]] as Mr. Ogidan\n* [[Wale Akorede]] as Baba Nepa\n* [[Charles Okocha]] as Emeka\n* [[Halimat Adegbola]] as Mama Goke\n* [[Tobi Bakre]] as Goke\n* [[Simi (singer)|Simi]]\n\n== Synopsis ==\nThe story revolves around a 11-year-old boy Ponmile (Toni Afolayan), who is from the middle class suburbs spends the day as a lowly apprentice at a mechanic worship in order to view and glance the life from other angles. When his father arrives to take home; Ponmile has to make up his mind if he wants to returns to school or take on his apprenticeship for full-time on a long-term basis.<ref>{{Citation|title=Mechanic (Mokalik) (2019)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/mechanic_2019|language=en|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\nThe filmmaker Kunle Afolayan cast his nephew Toni Afolayan in the main lead role who also eventually made his acting debut. Popular singer Simi also made her acting debut through this project and Tobi Bakre who participated in the ''[[Big Brother Naija (season 3)]]'' also made his acting debut. The film was predominantly shot in a mechanical village and also in [[Agege]] and [[Lagos]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title=5 things you should know about Kunle Afolayan\u2019s new movie, \u2018Mokalik\u2019|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/mokalik-5-things-you-should-know-about-kunle-afolayans-new-movie/qgtxk79|date=2019-03-28|website=Pulse Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref> The post-production works were done in Nigeria. The film was shot with a special flexible cinema camera [[Canon EOS C300 Mark II]] camera.<ref name=\":0\" /> The film directed revealed that this film was made with the intention of releasing it in Yoruba language as it was his first major film in the Yoruba language.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Why I made 'Mokalik' - Kunle Afolayan - P.M. News|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2019/08/04/why-i-made-mokalik-kunle-afolayan/|website=www.pmnewsnigeria.com|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|Nigeria}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{IMDb title|id=tt10327136}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy films]]\n[[Category:Nigerian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Nigerian films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Yoruba-language films]]\n[[Category:Films by Nigerian directors]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Lagos]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2019 Nigerian comedy drama film by Kunle Afolayan}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mokalik\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Kunle Afolayan]]\n| producer       = Kunle Afolayan\n| screenplay     = Tunde Babalola\n| story          = Kunle Afolayan\n| starring       = Toni Afolayan<br>[[Femi Adebayo]]<br>[[Tobi Bakre]]\n| music          = Kentoxygen Egunjobi\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio         = Golden Effects Pictures/Africa Magic\n| distributor    = FilmOne\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|05|31|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 99 minutes\n| country        = Nigeria\n| language       = English<br>Yoruba\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \u20a646.9[[million]]<ref name=cinema>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ceanigeria.com/box-office/2019-overall/122-top-20-wa-films-of-2019|title=TTop 20 films of 2019|publisher=Cinema Exhibitors Association of Nigeria}}</ref>\n| based on       = \n}}\n\n'''''Mokalik''''' ({{lang-en|Mechanic}}) is a 2019 Nigerian bilingual [[Comedy film|comedy]] [[Drama film|drama]] film produced and directed by veteran filmmaker [[Kunle Afolayan]]. The film stars newcomer Toni Afolayan in the male lead role along with [[Femi Adebayo]]. The film had its theatrical release on 31 May 2019 and received extremely positive reviews from critics while also performing well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Movie Review: Kunle Afolayan\u2019s \u2018Mokalik\u2019 thrives on memory, not viewer satisfaction|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/entertainment/nollywood/365003-movie-review-kunle-afolayans-mokalik-thrives-on-memory-not-viewer-satisfaction.html|date=2019-11-24|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Box Office: Nigerian moviegoers spent N636 million in July but less than N20